-- Braves Trainer Jeff Porter’s Wife Killed in Crash With Police Cruiser
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-01T06:37:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/braves-trainer-jeff-porter-s-wife-killed-in-crash-with-police-cruiser.html
The wife of Braves head athletic
trainer Jeff Porter was killed yesterday when the family’s sport
utility vehicle collided with a Georgia State Patrol cruiser,
the team said on its website.  Kathy Porter, 54, was killed. Porter and his 19-year-old
son David were treated for injuries.  “The Braves family is deeply saddened and shocked to learn
about the tragic accident involving the family of head athletic
trainer Jeff Porter and the death of his wife, Kathy,” the team
said.  Porter, who joined the Braves in 1985, has been head
athletic trainer since 2003.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  